# Architecture

## Component Hierarchy

```
app/layout.tsx
  └── Providers (providers/Providers.tsx)
        └── AppLayout (components/AppLayout.tsx)
              ├── Header (components/Header.tsx)
              ├── NavDrawer (components/NavDrawer.tsx)
              └── page.tsx
                    └── Playground (components/Playground.tsx)
                          └── GraphiQLWrapper (components/GraphiQLWrapper.tsx)
                                ├── OperationExplorer (sidebar)
                                └── GraphiQL (from graphiql package)
```

## Data Flow for Query Execution

1. `usePlayground` connects to endpoint, introspects schema, generates operations
2. `Playground` passes `schema`, `operations`, `token`, `activeEndpoint` to `GraphiQLWrapper`
3. `GraphiQLWrapper` wraps in `RequestTimingProvider` and renders `GraphiQLWrapperInner`
4. `useGraphiQL` hook manages editor key, storage, fetcher, and `handleAddOperation`
5. `OperationExplorer` sidebar lists queries/mutations; click calls `handleAddOperation`
6. `handleAddOperation` writes to storage and remounts `<GraphiQL>` via key change

## API Routes

| Route                    | Purpose                          |
|--------------------------|----------------------------------|
| `/api/introspect`        | Schema introspection via proxy   |
| `/api/graphql-proxy`     | GraphQL query execution proxy    |
| `/api/auth-login`        | Authentication token retrieval   |

## Storage

- `lib/storage.ts` manages `localStorage` for endpoints, tokens, active endpoint
- GraphiQL uses its own namespaced `localStorage` via `@graphiql/toolkit`'s `createLocalStorage`
- Namespace format: `graphql-playground:{endpointId}:{key}`
